TREASURY SURPLUS\nNOW $218,279,937\nIncome Tax and Re\nceipts Account for Ejtesss\nOver Same Period of Pre\nceding Year J\nWashington, Jan. 4 \u2014IAD-WSSk*\nrreamJfy ended the first half ofiis'iis\noal year with a surplus of ,**13X78,-\n937 compared with *123,59000 for tfie\nsame period a year ago. Income tax\nand c ustoms receipts, flowing in dur\ning the last quarter in aicreasing\namounts accounted for most of the\nexcess.\nDuring the year ending December 31\nthe treasury reduced the public debt\nby $1,173,504,301 to a total of *19,074,-\n665,337. Of the reduction. *314,353,900\nwas accomplished during the last\nmonth.\nCustoms receipts for the first six\nmonths of the present fiscal year\namounted to *318,817,857 compared\nwith *292,821,815 a year ago. A total\nof *48,431 263 was collected from cus\ntoms in December, or *2,000,009 more\nthan last December. Income tax col\nis for the six months were *l,\u00ab\n046.840.959 compared with *853.739.011\na year ago. In December these re\nceipts totaled $429,228,919. aII\nMiscellaneous taxes, many of which\nwere repealed by the new revenue law,\nyielded only $334,456,346 for the first\nsix months of this fiscal ye*# com\npared with *487,889.572 a year ask,\nAlthough calculations based on the\nfigures for the first six months would\nshow a surplus of almost *550,000.00*\nfor the year. Under-Seeretary Win3toa\n[declared the surplus would be about\n*333.000,000. He said the margin for\nthe first six months was cut yesterday\nby the appropriation of $123,000,000\n;to the fund for veterans' adjusted\nservice certificates.\nCOMBINEIAKES OFF\u00ae\nFOR SCHULTE COMMtMI\nNew York, Dec. 29\u2014(API\u2014ctec\ntors of the newly oi ganized-AMiAI 4k\ni United Tobaceo corporation, designed\nlas a holding company for the stock*\nof the United Cigar Stores company of\nAmerica, Schuite Retail Stores cor\nporation and other tobacco\nI panies. today offered Schulte stock\nholders one-half shares of Uajen 4k\nUnited common and *5 in cash for\n[each share of Schulte oommejvr,.;, The\n\u25a0offer expires January 15.\n-After negotiations lasting over firs\nyears the Union United company,was\norganized under the laws of Mary-\nI land to bring into closer working ar.\nrangements the two largest working\nI chain store tobacco companies in the\nworld. The Union United corpora\ntion has an authorized capital of\n300,000 shares of preferred stock of no\npar value and 2.000,000 share* of BO\n[par common, of which 250,000 shares\nof common have been issued- Offer*\nfor an exchange of stock of the Union\nUnited for that of other com panies\nwill be made later. :qHI\n13","height":"25750","width":"20036"}}
